Sure, here's an example of how to add a button that says "Hey there" using HTML and CSS:

HTML code:

```html
<button class="hey-btn">Hey there</button>
```

CSS code:

```css
.hey-btn {
  background-color: #007bff;
  color: #fff;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 4px;
  cursor: pointer;
  font-size: 16px;
}

.hey-btn:hover {
  background-color: #0062cc;
}
```

You can customize the styles as per your preference.
